	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: RockNES - NES emulator for Windows [5.52] 07/14/2017</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Attached find a Nintendulator source file that runs both <em>Skull &amp; Crossbones</em>, <em>Hard Drivin'</em>, <em>Rolling Thunder</em> (U.S. version) and <em>Xybots</em> like in the various videos I posted. Basically, I am making two assumptions that are not described in the wiki:<ol style="list-style-type: decimal"><li>It's not IRQcounter=IRQlatch +1, but IRQcounter=IRQlatch |1.</li><li>The |1 part is only done if the write sequence is C000 C001 E001 (as in Skull &amp; Crossbones). If the write sequence is C001 C000 E001 (as in Hard Drivin'), then the IRQcounter is loaded with the unmodified IRQlatch.</li></ol>These two assumptions should be testable with real hardware.

		
			<br clear="all" /><br />

